    <Folder>
      <name>Fishing locations</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Applegate Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7ZfaC7QQKKdVLw_O1MFUsEth7eDBwVTVOIxhIIAB_1XFsHfsLhAvJ_PvZYBx2E_gi9c9JMOeMA6tD_hMJ0WWU_ektYRSA1E0SX9rLh_Ejg87AXTsIyl_mLbauovQds8ez9rbiswqGqwWT6qtTmUQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 988-acre reservoir in southwestern Oregon just north of the California border. The lake was created in 1980 by damming the mainstream of the Applegate River 47 miles upstream from its confluence with the Rogue. It is named after Lindsay Applegate, a prominent early Oregon pioneer. This lake is located in the Skskiyou Mountains within the Rogue River-Siskiyou National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/rogue-siskiyou/). This is a flood control reservoir and depth varies dramatically between spring and fall.<br><br> <br>The lake is popular for cycling, boating, canoeing, fishing and hiking the various trails near the lake. The elevation of the lake is 1,987 feet. Camping: Camping is available at Hart-Tish (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea?recid=70232&actid=29),and Watkins (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/camping-cabins/recarea?recid=70404&actid=29) campgrounds. Dispersed hike-in camping is also available around the reservoir at French Gulch, Latgawa Cove, Streamtown, Harr Point and Tipsu Tyee campgrounds. Seattle Bar is a day-use only area at the south end of the reservoir. Jackson Picnic Park and Flumet Flat campgrounds are located about 5.6 miles downstream from the reservoir. Fees at some locations. Private concessionaire available seasonally.<br> <br>Boaters are subject to a 10 m.p.h. speed limit.<br><br>Fish species: trout, chinook slamon, largemouth bass, smallmouth bass, crappie<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7ZfaC7QQKKdVLw_O1MFUsEth7eDBwVTVOIxhIIAB_1XFsHfsLhAvJ_PvZYBx2E_gi9c9JMOeMA6tD_hMJ0WWU_ektYRSA1E0SX9rLh_Ejg87AXTsIyl_mLbauovQds8ez9rbiswqGqwWT6qtTmUQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.125603,42.050838,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Arizona Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a one-acre pond located at Arizona Beach State Park Recreation Area (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_258.php) approximately 15 miles south of Port Orford (http://www.portorford.org/). It is stocked with catchable and trophy trout in the spring and early summer. Fishing can be good all summer, depending on water conditions and stocking level. The pond has good bank access and a great place for kids to fish. The pond is managed for youths 17 and under.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.391327,42.608822,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bluebill Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5_u-3JFkiUGr8M4jfzuvMxs0hdlDajtWyydEvX54dNfy59syg-_9Bu71x7CRfavgg3ICyH8n0XWcBLC_nnqyYKw9_ZOBByJco-sOTOpTt0YdaI4zCvPMxAHOmHU64Z-OoyHVTrq0E_aDbucZfIxOInwg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This lake is located within the Oregon Dunes National Recreation Area (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c5/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72DTgBAjAwgAykeaxcN4jhYG_h4eYX5hPgYwefy6w0H24dcPNgEHcDTQ9_PIz03VL8iNMMgycVQEAObEnGA!/dl3/d3/L2dJQSEvUUt3QS9ZQnZ3LzZfME80MEkxVkFCOTBFMktTNUJIMjAwMDAwMDA!?navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&recid=42465&actid=&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&ss=110612&position=&ttype=recarea&pname=Siuslaw%2520National%2520Forest%2520-%2520Oregon%2520Dunes%2520National%2520Recreation%2520Area) about 3 miles north of North Bend, Ore. Nearby Bluebill Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c4/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72BTJw8jAwjQL8h2VAQAzHJMsQ!!?ss=110612&ttype=recarea&recid=42647&actid=31&navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&position=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&cid=null&pname=Oregon+Dunes+National+Recreation+Area+-+Bluebill+Campground) has camping sites for tents, cars, RVs and trailers. A one-mile hiking trail circles the lake.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5_u-3JFkiUGr8M4jfzuvMxs0hdlDajtWyydEvX54dNfy59syg-_9Bu71x7CRfavgg3ICyH8n0XWcBLC_nnqyYKw9_ZOBByJco-sOTOpTt0YdaI4zCvPMxAHOmHU64Z-OoyHVTrq0E_aDbucZfIxOInwg</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.261594,43.44918,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bolan Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Species Stocked: rainbow trout<br><br>Description: 13 acres surface area on USFS property<br><br>Amenities: primitive boat ramp. <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.458921,42.022979,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bradley Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ZYB6jP7dXBuLB0qaAWJ8fqVpyITIksucdVtCoV7uhf4YstPyDfO2GJkYne4Kfr38Gt2yY8D_sbJtTXi13N9Mi72JL9VMqxFYxjBVrOSYvTgE1U_pfpVoImYSc2Z886W2ESzHbLi7VWlCtXaIYzHQWZEmLnQ76LFPNTA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 30-acre lake about three miles north of Bandon, Ore. ODFW owns a boat ramp. Bank fishing is limited because most of the lakeshore is privately owned.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass<br><br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)<br><br><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7uCdG9cuM-jHJ2t5SaNTKiMD72eTtaLvdqPmpa3ZMBU1c" height="200" width="auto" />]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4ZYB6jP7dXBuLB0qaAWJ8fqVpyITIksucdVtCoV7uhf4YstPyDfO2GJkYne4Kfr38Gt2yY8D_sbJtTXi13N9Mi72JL9VMqxFYxjBVrOSYvTgE1U_pfpVoImYSc2Z886W2ESzHbLi7VWlCtXaIYzHQWZEmLnQ76LFPNTA https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7uCdG9cuM-jHJ2t5SaNTKiMD72eTtaLvdqPmpa3ZMBU1c</value>
