        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.265615,42.699252,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Eel Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7iQ4V85Qf1vMbvoNDP7Ln_7kYdmGD4u-eKwKzEenbVyhVhCFZYRjBPUbAiJQXD0QnVrp9c8mN60C2dV9SbBOOJH54m8zyQLGty_0revwN4HpAjjenEPcX-DGcZfm5Yp2WEnQ2s4P8UkwePcb22" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 355-acre lake located along Hwy. 101 approximately 13 miles north of North Bend, Ore. It consists of two long narrow arms in the shape of a U. Tugman State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_98.php) is adjacent to the lake and has both a boat ramp and an accessible fishing pier.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat troutm largemouth bass, smallmouth bass, yellow perch<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7iQ4V85Qf1vMbvoNDP7Ln_7kYdmGD4u-eKwKzEenbVyhVhCFZYRjBPUbAiJQXD0QnVrp9c8mN60C2dV9SbBOOJH54m8zyQLGty_0revwN4HpAjjenEPcX-DGcZfm5Yp2WEnQ2s4P8UkwePcb22</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.177351,43.604091,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Emigrant Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v75BHLmASt5e5_5UvBZfkUS8-JCUWtzVanpuU2I31R_NhJpNtQCIQqFCOEiiEwyx9Xp_lYgVY6r7CAZnjOSRVX-EPZ6ruLnNXB8o-o0TuYlc8l_8KLA57acfLWIT0xRYKSx4Rf090PMSACb8K8vS-kT8biMU5PE2A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Emigrant Lake is one of the most popular recreational destinations in Jackson County, Oregon. This lake has numerous amenities including developed campgrounds and picnic areas, two boat ramps, restrooms with showers. Reservations are recommended to camp at Emigrant Lake County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3525).<br> <br>Caution: This reservoir is listed under a health advisory for high levels of mercury. The health advisory suggests that anglers only eat trout stocked in the reservoir because they have not had as much time to absorb mercury as fish that spend their whole life in the reservoir.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, smallmouth bass, black crappie<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v75BHLmASt5e5_5UvBZfkUS8-JCUWtzVanpuU2I31R_NhJpNtQCIQqFCOEiiEwyx9Xp_lYgVY6r7CAZnjOSRVX-EPZ6ruLnNXB8o-o0TuYlc8l_8KLA57acfLWIT0xRYKSx4Rf090PMSACb8K8vS-kT8biMU5PE2A</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.616997,42.15961,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Empire Lakes</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Empire Lakes are two lakes located in northwest Coos Bay, Ore. The lakes are located in John Topits Park, a 120-acre park, which has a boat ramp, day use area, picnic tables, benches, and swimming beach. The lakes are surrounded by forests accessible by more than five miles of mostly paved walking trails. Motorized boats are not permitted on the lakes.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, bass, bluegill, perch catfish<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.262962,43.396703,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Expo Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v79iDaGRvAIRfBd1ejeMKmm2apzwDaIyvpjBjgBnvnBoGNvAw9_G0k52D8ih1VurdQuoXWVeBilexsSKVDIJeJNs9WSoCn5UkaHtFvzXlgWGxtYzJ2hCvPbVHT8JIaSMyy40sUcPvAuwhAWd_z86A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This pond is located at the Jackson County Fairgrounds in Central Point, Ore., just north of the Expo buildings. Easy bank access makes this a good choice for younger anglers.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v79iDaGRvAIRfBd1ejeMKmm2apzwDaIyvpjBjgBnvnBoGNvAw9_G0k52D8ih1VurdQuoXWVeBilexsSKVDIJeJNs9WSoCn5UkaHtFvzXlgWGxtYzJ2hCvPbVHT8JIaSMyy40sUcPvAuwhAWd_z86A</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.913837,42.388822,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Fish Lake - Rogue Watershed</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4Vb4Km5WB7nPxPSMjMrSf9GxZnqo5WzS3TNaZB7A7YcgDkwQVooscr-_T1WW33tECRCjVowlscxsSXcrYQcQ8_hXt0jBHlSZ0JKnPvMCCE5UVpLs6VqCQHMWVBEPldxeLUbt30Xq66figpfeg2Mg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Fish Lake is a 483-acre lake in southern Oregon about 35 miles northeast of Medford.<br> <br>The lake has a maximum depth of 31 feet and an average depth of 18 feet. The lake is located within the Rogue River-Siskiyou National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/rogue-siskiyou/). Camping is available nearby at Fish Lake (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/recarea/?recid=69728), North Fork (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/recarea/?recid=69832) and Doe Point (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/recarea/?recid=69716) campgrounds. Popular activities include swimming, boating, hiking horseback riding, hunting, fishing and wildlife viewing. This is one of only two lakes in Oregon where tiger trout are being stocked on an experimental basis. Fish Lake Resort (http://www.fishlakeresort.net/) offers rental cabins, RV sites, primitive campsites, boat rentals and moorage. Boaters are subject to a 10 m.p.h. speed limit.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout, tiger trout, spring chinook<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4Vb4Km5WB7nPxPSMjMrSf9GxZnqo5WzS3TNaZB7A7YcgDkwQVooscr-_T1WW33tECRCjVowlscxsSXcrYQcQ8_hXt0jBHlSZ0JKnPvMCCE5UVpLs6VqCQHMWVBEPldxeLUbt30Xq66figpfeg2Mg</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.319653,42.394202,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Floras Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 250-acre lake located about 17 miles south of Bandon, Ore. The lake has a healthy population of cutthroat trout and some largemouth bass. The lake is also stocked with catchable and trophy trout in the spring. Access to the lake is mainly by boat as bank access is limited. This lake reaches a maximum depth of about 50 feet. Boice-Cope County Park (http://www.co.curry.or.us/parks/parks.htm) provides camping and a boat ramp.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.502134,42.901684,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Garrison Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 134-acre lake located in Port Orford, Ore. It is stocked several times in the spring with trophy and catchable trout. Fishing can be good through May but warmer water and aquatic weeds make for tough fishing through summer. The best way to fish the lake is by boat but bank fishing can be good of the fishing pier on 12th street. Boat ramps are located at 12th Street and Pinehurst Roads. Anglers should keep an eye on the weather and target the lake when winds are light. <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.5081,42.75571,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Howard Prairie Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7LX5Mdw3txSwzZfgZKWriVWqEP9ceeuinuQMuaz-zYOXCAhY4e5_8vp9SMGg7j68oVOhWsHFYU1J309GDhsOEfppK22CDCWpjJgfVpUoJIwlC8BMvjakCMsei9P6CvtFiv2l8H2zd2EWuC189Atqm2JW0pBoNnBG4" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Howard Prairie Lake is a popular destination in sourthern Oregon that offers an abundance of recreational opportunities, including excellent trout and bass fishing. This 1,990-acre reservoir is located about 43 miles south of Medford and 24 miles east of Ashland. It has a maximum depth of 80 feet and an average depth of 35 feet. The lake is formed by the 100-foot tall Howard Prairie Dam, which impounds Beaver Creek, in the Klamath River watershed.<br> <br>Amenities: Asperkaha Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3535), Grizzly County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3536), Klum Landing County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3537), Lily Glen County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3538), Sugar Pine County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3539), Willow Point County Park (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3529), The Resort at Howard Prairie Lake<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, bass<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
