            -122.410505,42.240131,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Hyatt Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5Xi-ClgRESu5qkB9zKs5BzetDApjsmr7Nb4rA6BPCC5PJsj1xhY0tbQiY_yf45JpZj-yhx4XmwnnwS9WW7k1V6_lbGh9K7jH3yPwHgkm58WlDffL2BMsxEHvLBaiUVRQxsV7NFnA-DNbi4oJgHMe321kC_tA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 950-acre reservoir about 13 miles east of Ashland, Ore. There is a large BLM campground (http://www.blm.gov/or/resources/recreation/site_info.php?siteid=135) with boat ramp at the south end of the reservoir. Boats are restricted to 10 m.p,h. on this lake<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
