            -122.46829,42.173137,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lake Selmac</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6d4c8dBiNEdGV0wZOJrduqFpJXeBlCXm85Nzh_i3vE10Sqthexg--yF-bzuaJPg9OYYXWgijNm4H8frjN9b8vVjuE5-Zs6D4HVRAtjElfIfIZu36xj9eBkZTfsmK8SPwxxpZS3gPlEW9T7yGRH8tak" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Lake Selmac is a 160-acre lake in Josephine County, approximately 25 miles southwest of Grants Pass, Ore. Four campgrounds are located within close proximity of the lake. There is a boat ramp and dock at Lake Selmac County Park (http://www.co.josephine.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=492) on the south shore of the lake. Boats are restricted to a maximum speed of 5 m.p.h.<br> <br>Amenities -- Boat ramp, boat rentals, tent and RV camp sites, yurts, day use picnic areas, fire rings and barbecues, restrooms, vault toilets, trail system, disc golf course, baseball field.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, bass, crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6d4c8dBiNEdGV0wZOJrduqFpJXeBlCXm85Nzh_i3vE10Sqthexg--yF-bzuaJPg9OYYXWgijNm4H8frjN9b8vVjuE5-Zs6D4HVRAtjElfIfIZu36xj9eBkZTfsmK8SPwxxpZS3gPlEW9T7yGRH8tak</value>
