      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Medco Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7hqOSPe8zky21a-dWj1i9mEW9r_LG-BRXq6vtSKFigDKwZuTW1ge-Q_CaNkzC6x2HVGhQ-Haiug57C-SeKECrtg2JjcZhTc7-QotnTncTQ-5L7UcHz7Sb5nGn0tHyU19NTo-vclFc5yMTx9SBiZY0DxQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This a 25-acre pond located between Prospect and Butte Falls northeast of Medford, Oregon. The pond is privately owned by the Swanson Group, an Oregon-based timber company, but is open to the public. The pond is surrounded by pine trees, and behind an earthen dam across the pond is an additional 40 acres of lilly pad water. Amenities are limited, consisting of a couple of port-a-potties and some picnic tables.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
