      <Placemark>
        <name>Powers Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7LQi9OOjiMczBATgqvuu6Zw1e03NP15nZSpLPlndjDylQ2RC_gyiVlu2qyKQpzwg1mwPgVqNeb8tDThVrS-tq-rpiFVijeW3ZUM-AYDitfcY5MKCx7Y_NABmJX1F2KpUh8m-_T_ISX-P1ww499Q2ss" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 23-acre former mill pond located in Powers Park next to the Coquille River in the southwest Oregon town of Powers. The park has RV facilities, showers and a picnic area.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, black crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead.   ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
