      <Placemark>
        <name>Reinhart Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5xV_EKCaMrRf73i7Zazua8OlaMuUg_uDofgCrg1A-bVodoKDO8c4Wyf6rod5vxcIAwqXeEj6xBAfRzfxjloOEYcVWftZkQUI7DlwQiOtKkTf3M5tPsgBjuI3xXUcfrUihWgEGSp20SoVVN54uRF7WX4Xo" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This pond is located within Reinhart Volunteer Park (http://www.grantspassoregon.gov/Index.aspx?page=158) at 1690 SW Webster Rd. in Grants Pass, Ore. Amenities at this riverside park include softball and baseball fields, a soccer field, sand vollehyball courts, flycasting pond, jogging trail, tennis and basketball courts, and shelters available for reservations.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
