      <Placemark>
        <name>Rogue River above Lost Creek</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5of75kg3gdQPmxN_eV7K7LaLcy1ok5Z5Sc5ipNb8cJaBFyraEpiMgi-0ESWs9ZLc15ppVgaJKCpuSJGq6oT87e7gyuTSebYlk_x6VYB6ICNyL7US1QrOCAh-r6gAumKjFaLcQq7XeSFo8UePwuUpuKS1_0H6AfGDq7Nct91Psghng" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This beautiful section of the Rogue River is stocked with rainbow trout regularly throughout the summer. Much of this section of the river is within the Rogue River-Siskiyou National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/rogue-siskiyou/). A maintained trail follows the entire length of this section of the river, and U.S. Forest Service campgrounds and day-use areas are available<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, brook trout, brown trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
