      <Placemark>
        <name>Saunders Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4WZhYJTaegFln8qaOuPYsS9VGIVbwqHgOM9YGaN_32UsSFWJvS3pH3E8d7XQq-8KnPachb4tu8uzmDMXHvTZMPPdioxjrWYL9DMRA_VY552PPjwvuGAYEsTkbiOURAYOqmcAZdRgPP-dl3bPO13FT35A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 55-acre lake west of Hwy. 101 about 15 miles south of Reedsport, Ore. There is a county park with a picnic area, boat ramp and bank fishing at the south end of the lake. The rest of the lake shore is residential land and no camping is allowed. However, campgrounds are located north about 3-6 miles at Tenmile and Eel lakes<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
