      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Spalding Pond</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5BlEhdW2Ex0slF8V6PTOKiyqagcf6mjBB2IFdGqf1mWWi4BWxjGB5593ehxwUbaEN2BpMdqzsXbZmNC0jXG7WejzRJvKAd_AC3aWPhZYGGW3mBdYRQcrMVywJtYuuZJ_dsvAK3OKi4ALGt8bGLcFmgeQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 3-acre lake located on a historic mill site within the Rogue River-Siskiyou National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/rogue-siskiyou/). It has three ADA accessible fishing platforms and a surfaced accessible trail in a primitive setting appr. 21 miles southwest of Grants Pass, Ore. There is an accessible restroom and small campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/recarea/?recid=70678). There is a small pebble beach.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5BlEhdW2Ex0slF8V6PTOKiyqagcf6mjBB2IFdGqf1mWWi4BWxjGB5593ehxwUbaEN2BpMdqzsXbZmNC0jXG7WejzRJvKAd_AC3aWPhZYGGW3mBdYRQcrMVywJtYuuZJ_dsvAK3OKi4ALGt8bGLcFmgeQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.704,42.346702,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Sru Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a small lake located appr. 21 miles southeast of Powers, Ore., on the Rogue-River-Siskiyou National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/main/rogue-siskiyou/home). Camping is available nearby at Sru Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/rogue-siskiyou/recreation/fishing/recarea/?recid=70098&actid=42).<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.005883,42.731867,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Tenmile Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7YmB9aalzNIYPSm86qaahZbJZERv-zITC1xDkyz0OriwgZ2JE8vY3bt1NgBschu38_85MC77wnAIDCQqMWPxTZyuz5DtQb0qCB_6CLoaLOMNCXfXBuAx7rT-Pd3nK3wuW5iFGNcHMMO3ki3yDPZx4BtA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Two large lakes on the Oregon coast next to the town of Lakeside in Coos County. The lakes have 170 miles of shoreline, a surface area of 2,723 acres and an average depth of about 15 feet. They have numerous bays, arms and fingers that hold a variety of trout and warmwater fish species. These lakes are considered one of Oregon's premier warmwater fisheries. The lake is located just minutes from the Oregon Dunes National Recreation Area, (http://www.fs.usda.gov/wps/portal/fsinternet/!ut/p/c5/04_SB8K8xLLM9MSSzPy8xBz9CP0os3gDfxMDT8MwRydLA1cj72DTgBAjAwgAykeaxcN4jhYG_h4eYX5hPgYwefy6w0H24dcPNgEHcDTQ9_PIz03VL8iNMMgycVQEAObEnGA!/dl3/d3/L2dJQSEvUUt3QS9ZQnZ3LzZfME80MEkxVkFCOTBFMktTNUJIMjAwMDAwMDA!/?navtype=BROWSEBYSUBJECT&recid=42465&actid=&navid=110000000000000&pnavid=&ss=110612&position=&ttype=recarea&pname=Siuslaw%20National%20Forest%20-%20Oregon%20Dunes%20National%20Recreation%20Area) which has numerous campgrounds, hiking trails, and other recreational amenities.<br> <br>Amenities: county park, two boat ramps, three marinas<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass, crappie, bluegill, yellow perch, brown bullhead<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7YmB9aalzNIYPSm86qaahZbJZERv-zITC1xDkyz0OriwgZ2JE8vY3bt1NgBschu38_85MC77wnAIDCQqMWPxTZyuz5DtQb0qCB_6CLoaLOMNCXfXBuAx7rT-Pd3nK3wuW5iFGNcHMMO3ki3yDPZx4BtA</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
