      <Placemark>
        <name>Willow Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7F-DQSqR_Qw-2YDzJfKoKbuk1yHVLBOgF3TXtbgjSVkquWKrZ16bS00bLa0j5m28BG3LN8xdNpqFHQCpgp4QTNNGT28CnoFRSsriVrTQuoe5tDsLsjOd7_0ykf6lRea0_8rhd8CQgwp-0W8wG_IQMH" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Willow Lake is a popular southern Oregon reservoir which stores the waters of Willow Creek, a tributary of the South Fork of Big Butte Creek. The 52-foot high, earthfill dam was completed in 1952 by the Medford Water Commission to store water as part of their municipal water system. The lake is located at the base of Mt. McLoughlin on land owned by Jackson County. It is located approximately 7.5 miles east of Butte Falls and 43 miles northeast of Medfore, Ore. Jackson County has designated the surrounding 927 acres as a recreational area, which provides a number of amenities, including campsites, RV sites, cabins, picnic area, restrooms, and boat ramp.<br> <br>Amenities: Willow Lake County Park<br> (http://www.co.jackson.or.us/Page.asp?NavID=3514)<br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, kokanee, largemouth bass, black crappie, brown bullhead<br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-53</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7F-DQSqR_Qw-2YDzJfKoKbuk1yHVLBOgF3TXtbgjSVkquWKrZ16bS00bLa0j5m28BG3LN8xdNpqFHQCpgp4QTNNGT28CnoFRSsriVrTQuoe5tDsLsjOd7_0ykf6lRea0_8rhd8CQgwp-0W8wG_IQMH</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.457894,42.469386,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
