      <name>Umpqua Roseburg Office 541-440-3353</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Ben Irving Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4XCWDbexUFRvkdzPDmAJCDmun9gs8tVnMPtt3hIqL6GWoEdBPacI5WtCO4czM7QDMY8zK8ZA0k3Se1epIm1QerTQcdfSYMfmI4IjeEE-epvsscIrHBwotkS2eQsEDknrQybz1VjzUD9PWpinSiRORgl6k" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 250-acre lake in Douglas County, Oregon, created by the construction of Berry Creek Dam, which impounds Berry Creek. The reservoir is named for a longtime Oregon outdoorsman and is located in a narrow canyon about 10 miles southwest of Winston, Oregon. Boats are allowed on the reservoir, which is popular for water skiing, butthere is an electric motor only section for angling.<br> <br>Amenities: boat ramp, picnic tables, barbecue, restroom<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill, yellow perch, black crappie, brown bullhead<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
