      <Placemark>
        <name>Buckeye Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_Gzme3ZlRwURjp-_KfQE4QYpBYdlTI0TK2USTIXp8o3wBPTlUTH0JuJxFWefcy3YzVt0e9tfRnLdby2AXVP3zZPoWNXy71egBfzxRdYdum0wvQDaKqHpSJg0WBpqfnTEylGoTxZ7Zi8jw4JLx1MeWxAx4KAPiOlrBVgz6DcQW_o2XRIIjFdudAY0fWV7WN_AieQQ-2aB?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 10-acre hike-in lake located within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua/). There are improved campgrounds nearby at Buckeye and Cliff Lake. The lake is annually stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, eastern brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
