      <Placemark>
        <name>Bull Pup Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6OwJDlsQeG0B3jtGwCnLp5g6gfsedvaVHrq5WtSRSo3UmmqvpNks72VSJnXhroDkPEAc8QtMTlEVn1OkmD8mKbwFCT5p8NZW2yHYjoQ3gg4iVADeuxXXf8JOzf_PHtJZLpQRb3ziO5uCljinBF5kRIcg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This lake is located in the North Umpqua watershed within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua) east of Roseburg, Ore. The lake is annually stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
