      <Placemark>
        <name>Calamut Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5-ZR0toMTljAS6ip3GwPorySfbQA9TU2EviT-ksDHQm-TqYYsn4bD-YNR5UhoLDYY92WCkYwrrCQ18-Z40joHjEYfclra4AIp3OLQtkEZDW1kzCOH92FhorXk6lV8sGCIusnRGb9arGPqejCngQm_4-A" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is an 18-acre hike-in Lake located within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua/). There are a few improved campsites at the lake. The lake is stocked annually with fingerling Rainbow Trout<br> <br>Fish species: eastern brook trout, rainbow trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
