      <Placemark>
        <name>Cliff Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://mymaps.usercontent.google.com/hostedimage/m/*/3AE5a_Gy9CKYYRlKt5cFJvuOLQtFBBj6x6ef4P0rAtRvyBFUa0pvtjp3-Gf1bpXqCpz397ua1OHyX39VDOd3J9KjM6JU8IyMllTEr_wzftIlqc1dTuFXrwo7Gn_BffW-q6UKBVV7c7L7SrZCXyFoxZH9UtnmZM7mICScwTpp8mn3cFmMpdylEBQyD1xRIVwnDQH7Pm0i-VEPP?fife=s16383" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 7-acre hike-in lake located within the Umpqua National Forest in the Rogue Umpqua Divide Wilderness. (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua). Skimmerhorn Trail 1578 offers the most direct way in. Campsites are nearby at Cliff and Buckeye. The lake is annually stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, eastern brook trout<br><br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
