      <Placemark>
        <name>Cooper Creek Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4A9JFN0b9Cbfq_EQuG7ygzy8B6hLGv5E19pdeZrRAqFUMeWJdzK454vu_5FDnhxVVLgIUVBMVNFXYIZIyFtrhc8I7EtVsnQRpmKJjeL895bnS_jx5oDDbh_x-CUBGMjGmljUYo06Pi4c1VyAfRf0nfAQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 160-acre reservoir located about three miles east of Sutherlin, Oregon in the Umpqua River Basin. Boating is allowed and the reservoir is popular for waterskiing but there are still several fingers good for fishing as well as a speed limit zone near the boat ramp.<br> <br>Amenities: two boat ramps, pavilion, picnic area, restroom, barbecue<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill, yellow perch, brown bullhead, black crappie, yellow bullhead<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4A9JFN0b9Cbfq_EQuG7ygzy8B6hLGv5E19pdeZrRAqFUMeWJdzK454vu_5FDnhxVVLgIUVBMVNFXYIZIyFtrhc8I7EtVsnQRpmKJjeL895bnS_jx5oDDbh_x-CUBGMjGmljUYo06Pi4c1VyAfRf0nfAQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
