            -123.275185,43.376419,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Diamond Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v4qlLAh9Q4XH5pLF1NVXvWhgD6e4aw0YyokyXCDZtsPE77qqi5W-Q9RhNDV4dKw_2Z3rgtWrvrUs2gBPxVPQhZLIhjCHiFK8Vkjf9Aft6ChyPv1Xgv2QDV2lrxcFEHSN5Zp97DUsxjK6vRbpeUKaeAYvQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Diamond Lake is a 2,824-acre lake within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua) in southern Oregon, just north of Crater Lake National Park (http://www.nps.gov/crla/index.htm) in Douglas County. This lake is one of the most popular recreational fisheries in southern Oregon. Fishing is done both from boats and from the bank. There are five paved boat ramps, three U.S. Forest Service campgrounds and a privately owned resort around Diamond Lake.<br> <br>Campgrounds: Diamond Lake Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63480), Broken Arrow Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63460), Thielson View Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63618)<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, tiger trout, brown trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
