      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Fuller Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5o_UcPrdqseis1FK_-WZN1vz3zTmEGWPsavR0G4D-q8lNx8LKMk94sx1U2vsd_qyPOcOKaE_gud19GCKAKXQFoFNOklYXjKmr5GD3WmQ9DvXhtYjvp2n-UEcKXO00a58uAalqs17k0iC13XzbBXtw" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This small lake is located within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/null/recarea/?recid=63696&actid=93) about 47 miles from Glide, Ore. A lakeside shelter is available. The lake is annually stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, eastern brook trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5o_UcPrdqseis1FK_-WZN1vz3zTmEGWPsavR0G4D-q8lNx8LKMk94sx1U2vsd_qyPOcOKaE_gud19GCKAKXQFoFNOklYXjKmr5GD3WmQ9DvXhtYjvp2n-UEcKXO00a58uAalqs17k0iC13XzbBXtw</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.494168,43.401337,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Galesville Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5asLMO6CMWeUYuCDP5IZ7U4dt7Fi69bPY-27qbSRFM_e6vJiCviPxnVhs2QhOv66Wsjyxo3TBQ6zJir5yXhOsf56jCRtLWmRhYcihLZDixtL4Z1ZFhelYAaHrJxcEUVwtSG5K1EdOQyhzK30IF-oz0em5RtdHEq2kg" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This 630-acre reservoir is open to angling year-round. In addition to trout, the reservoir is sometimes stocked with coho salmon smolts. Many people mistakenly think these fish are kokanee. All of the smolts are adipose fin-clipped. In this reservoir, all landlocked salmon are considered trout and are part of the five-per-day bag limit. This reservoir has a new campground in addition to the picnic area, plus two boat ramps.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, bluegill, brown bullhead, black crappie, cutthroat trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5asLMO6CMWeUYuCDP5IZ7U4dt7Fi69bPY-27qbSRFM_e6vJiCviPxnVhs2QhOv66Wsjyxo3TBQ6zJir5yXhOsf56jCRtLWmRhYcihLZDixtL4Z1ZFhelYAaHrJxcEUVwtSG5K1EdOQyhzK30IF-oz0em5RtdHEq2kg</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.158455,42.849289,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Hemlock Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5baeqo6sMXXtPIcvGGzjf5_aC1cylnYYVztyaMWt1N4pIqpx5e6i7fgJzBEh-163g-ZRQz67_0WDybTdOUyzBUSCethtgfJx_j8PMsHbMYSVfs15qrR0-mX948ZMm-ueQuaIsiq832sXxIVnH21Ql1" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This lake is situated in a secluded moutain setting in the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua) at an elevation of 4,000 feet. The lake is approximately 33 feet deep at its deepest point. There is a boat launch and 13 nearby campsites at Hemlock Meadows Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea/?recid=63708). Boats are stricted to electric motors only.<br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, kokanee<br><br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5baeqo6sMXXtPIcvGGzjf5_aC1cylnYYVztyaMWt1N4pIqpx5e6i7fgJzBEh-163g-ZRQz67_0WDybTdOUyzBUSCethtgfJx_j8PMsHbMYSVfs15qrR0-mX948ZMm-ueQuaIsiq832sXxIVnH21Ql1</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.69807,43.188305,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lake in the Woods - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 4-acre lake located in the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua) east of Roseburg, Ore. Motor boats are not allowed.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.7252115,43.2170694,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lake Marie</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v43NF2nHvy72U5prFVdtpudjV5GfhuGgQV4KHeYYSsdT3oBRsXA9hHZcdTmzZNEDjcAOPkK3drorNdVG2fwHKz-lB2cW9yF8_JUuRZDJddaxbAxD2KqEvSKlL8OVUT3sCQ2vCbWqA_OIA4nbgjbyEE" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 5-acre lake located in the Umpqua Lighthouse State Park (http://www.oregonstateparks.org/park_121.php) near Winchester Bay, Oregon. It has a sandy beach at one end for swimming and day use, and hiking trails around the perimeter. There is no boat ramp, and motor boats are prohibited.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, yellow perch<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v43NF2nHvy72U5prFVdtpudjV5GfhuGgQV4KHeYYSsdT3oBRsXA9hHZcdTmzZNEDjcAOPkK3drorNdVG2fwHKz-lB2cW9yF8_JUuRZDJddaxbAxD2KqEvSKlL8OVUT3sCQ2vCbWqA_OIA4nbgjbyEE</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -124.192865,43.660106,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lemolo Reservoir - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5i8Xk8vBtojpfkv88QuyBshqCFQGlfBbUPh3deeBozkgkYt2k7GtsJnr-fjWbhu6ADFAeTssS88oZMeUtt5Mt4FHk3-bP-NJby9H0n0p7_AdxBQK30hlbgvx1HF6EK2SltjQZtUpkxGQx4RPXAbqA" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 415-acre reservoir in the North Umpqua River basin. Three boat ramps, four campgrounds and resort are located on the lake. Lemolo Lake Resort (http://www.lemololakeresort.com/) offers gas, food, lodging, bait, tackle, boat rentals and launching. Spectacular views of the High Cascade Mountains can be seen from the lake. In the winter there is cross-country skiing and a wealth of snowmobile trails that lead through sparkling landscapes.<br> <br>Several Forest Service campgrounds are located in close proximity to the reservoir: Bunker Hill Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63466), East Lemolo Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63492), Inlet Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63508), Poole Creek Campground (http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/recarea?recid=63570)<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brown trout, kokanee<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v5i8Xk8vBtojpfkv88QuyBshqCFQGlfBbUPh3deeBozkgkYt2k7GtsJnr-fjWbhu6ADFAeTssS88oZMeUtt5Mt4FHk3-bP-NJby9H0n0p7_AdxBQK30hlbgvx1HF6EK2SltjQZtUpkxGQx4RPXAbqA</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.1934603,43.3143743,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Linda Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This lake is located within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua/). The trailhead for Calamut Lake begins here. The lake is stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, brook trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.1190702,43.3513845,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Loon Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 294-acre lake located in Douglas County about 15 miles southeast of Reedsport, Ore. There are two resorts and a BLM campground (http://www.blm.gov/or/resources/recreation/site_info.php?siteid=34) with a boat ramp on the north end of the lake. This lake is two miles long and reaches a maximum debth of 105 feet. Boats are allowed and this lake is popular for water skiing. However, it has a speed limit zone for fishing on the south end. It has both BLM and private resort campgrounds and boat ramps.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout, cutthroat trout, largemouth bass, black crappie, bluegill, brown bullhead<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.847075,43.596368,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Maidu Lake</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 20-acre hike-in lake located approximately 38 miles west of LaPine, Ore., at the head of the North Umpqua River. It is usually accessible by June. It is a 7-mile hike from the Kelsey Valley horse camp side and approximately 3 miles from the Miller Lake side. https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recreation/hiking/recarea/?recid=63738&actid=51. The lake is annually stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: brook trout, Rainbow Trout<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.001457,43.257112,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Plat I Reservoir</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7EqI2DhHqgP0r3GCpY4JOpxxHAcyI-LkfkcJ-mMNuxYuxRKrK1WABdImudoMcaS7LqQxxs4FEDJJ6IoVqwAVWDfP8kVE-CBheCsadERfLVE8Bi9xHGWRiw_sUtha_QpBzSW7QLlMEEWQuYBT98icoc" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>This is a 155-acre reservoir on Sutherlin Creek in Douglas County, Oregon. It is owned by Sutherlin Creek Water Control District and is open to fishing year-round. <br><br>Fish species: rainbow trout, largemouth bass, black crappie, brown bullhead<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v7EqI2DhHqgP0r3GCpY4JOpxxHAcyI-LkfkcJ-mMNuxYuxRKrK1WABdImudoMcaS7LqQxxs4FEDJJ6IoVqwAVWDfP8kVE-CBheCsadERfLVE8Bi9xHGWRiw_sUtha_QpBzSW7QLlMEEWQuYBT98icoc</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -123.252021,43.395779,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Red Top Pond - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This couple acre pond is situated near the headwaters of Deadman Creek in the Umpqua River basin. Fishing access includes bank, float tube, inflatable pontoon boat, and canoes. There is dispersed camping near the lake. The area around the lake is owned by the Cow Creek Tribe, please be respectful of the land.<br> <br>Fish species: rainbow trout<br><br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br>Trout Stocking Schedule (http://www.dfw.state.or.us/resources/fishing/trout_stocking_schedules/)<br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.956093,43.080381,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Skookum Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a 15-acre hike-in lake in the Umpqua River watershed. https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/umpqua/recarea/?recid=63600<br>The lake is stocked annually with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br> <br>Fish species: brook trout, Rainbow Trout.<br> <br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.336884,43.167502,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Twin Lakes - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6y6n26K1Ay7L11u2qwuP_rzI_0fF5JuuuKvSI1dRsThypCns3ZOXzj8-CbPHbJDwwXaSA3PTB0065UbES8rjjzcEb42_Dh7grzjel76RWyd8RoIz08Jjejzd2j-Vmr_dEFPKY97rpa6tRtW0OHqQ" height="200" width="auto" /><br><br>Two lakes located within the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua) in a secluded mountain setting. The larger of the two is a 12-acre lake, and the other is about half that size. Only the larger lake is stocked with fingerling Rainbow Trout. There is a primitive campground in the area.<br><br>Fish species: brook trout, Rainbow<br> <br><br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="gx_media_links">
            <value>https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/umsh/AN6v0v6y6n26K1Ay7L11u2qwuP_rzI_0fF5JuuuKvSI1dRsThypCns3ZOXzj8-CbPHbJDwwXaSA3PTB0065UbES8rjjzcEb42_Dh7grzjel76RWyd8RoIz08Jjejzd2j-Vmr_dEFPKY97rpa6tRtW0OHqQ</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.5896232,43.2295472,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Wolf Lake - Umpqua</name>
        <description><![CDATA[This is a small hike-in lake located in the Umpqua National Forest (http://www.fs.usda.gov/umpqua/). It has horse corrals at the trailhead. The lake is stock annually with fingerling Rainbow Trout.<br> <br>Fish species: brook trout, Rainbow Trout<br> <br>ODFW Recreation Report & regulation updates (http://myodfw.com/recreation-report/fishing-report/southwest-zone/)<br><br>Fishing Regulations (http://www.eregulations.com/oregon/fishing/)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -122.451296,43.149736,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
